HERE AND NOFURTHER dove inside nearing the half mile marker, eased out and edged up between runners approaching the quarter pole, shifted out to pursue in upper stretch, drop back in a bit to advance between horses leaving mid stretch and kept on gamely to gain the place. STREET HUSTLE vied three wide between runners heading to the turn, emerged in a battle outside HIS ROYAL G leaving the three eighths, gained a short lead in upper stretch then wandered out, was corrected with right handed asks, held a clear advantage past the eighth pole then gave way grudgingly. SHEER ELEMENT broke sluggishly, saved ground to upper stretch, eased out and offered a mild run. HE ROLLS disputed the pace inside runners to the half mile pole, chased around the turn then gave way through the drive. EL TOLU was shuffled back from between rivals after a furlong, dropped well back, raced two to three wide in upper stretch and failed to menace. SCORCHED BY FIRE , wide, was not a factor. AWESOME STEPHEN , four deep pressing the pace into the turn, pursued four wide around the turn then faltered in upper stretch.
